               <provenance><p>Probably owned by <persName role="collector">Édouard Ariel</persName> (1818-1854), as attested by the typical Ariel manuscript title page (U1), with shelfmark in black ink. There is however no BnF stamp <quote>DON N° <space type="vacat"/></quote>, as regularly found on Ariel manuscripts. If an Ariel manuscript, it is was bequested by Édouard Ariel to Société Asiatique (Rosny 1868, p. 177) and received by the BnF in 1866, then borrowed, used and returned Julien Vinson.</p></provenance></history>
